# `astro.config.mjs` & `src/content.config.ts`

Apply the relevant bullets when editing **either** `astro.config.mjs` or `src/content.config.ts`.

## `astro.config.mjs`

- **`site`:** Canonical origin (e.g. `https://yourdomain.com`). Affects sitemap, RSS `context.site`, and `Astro.site`. Update placeholder URLs in `src/components/fundations/head/Seo.astro` for production.
- **Stack:** Vite plugin `tailwindcss()`; integrations `mdx()`, `sitemap()`. Match existing patterns when adding or removing integrations.
- **`markdown` / Shiki:** Options here affect MD/MDX rendering globally.

## `src/content.config.ts`

- **Loaders:** `glob` loaders under `src/content/<collection>/`.
- **Zod:** Changing fields impacts all `getCollection` / `render` consumers in `src/pages/**` and `src/layouts/**` — update them in the same change.
- **`image()`:** Keep `store.thumbnail`, optional `store.images`, and `posts.image` aligned with layouts unless you refactor image handling everywhere.

## Coordination

- Most schema-only work touches **only** `src/content.config.ts` and consuming Astro files — not `astro.config.mjs`.
- Touch **both** when a feature needs build integration **and** content shape (e.g. new content loader type, markdown config tied to MDX).
- Do not widen content schemas without updating every page that reads those fields.
